    "body": "@glitchminer looks ok, but this is still overall criteria (what we want to have actually) without getting into and describing all possible states you may ran into from a certain screen (that depends a lot on the Keycard's state). \r\n\r\n- for almost all states before `Accounts on this keycard` (like `Insert this Keycard...`, `Reading Keycard...`, ...) we should display keypair at the bottom of those states even before we actually enter the pin and get the info what's really stored on a Keycard (we can do that, cause we're running into this flow from the card specific page, so we know which Keycard, containing which keypair we're asking user for)\r\n- `Extended accounts on this keycard` - this term doesn't exist and after entering the pin, you will get a list of accounts stored on a keycard, that's all, so it's enough to say `Accounts on this keycard`",
